                    "created": "2008-06-07T21:38:36.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-06-07T21:38:36.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/31103",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, this is the desired behavior. The goal of the rememberMe feature is to be able to modify the cookie_lifetime of an already started session, without destroying the existing session.  \n\nSo by setting the value of remember_me_seconds via an ini value, you are saying that when you call rememberMe(), it will use the value provided by the ini setting.\n\nTo be able to change the cookie lifetime for all sessions from when they first start, use the cookie_lifetime setting:\n\n{code}\nZend_Session::setOptions(array('cookie_lifetime' => $someLongValue));\n{code}\n\nIn summary the options are:\ncookie_lifetime - initial lifetime for all sessions\nremember_me_seconds - the value to chage the lifetime of a cookie to if this feature is opted into (thus, the application called Zend_Session::rememberMe())\n\nPresumably, by the time you get a screen to present the user with the rememberMe() feature, they have already started the default session in your application.\n\nMake sense?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ralph",
                        "name": "ralph",
                        "displayName": "Ralph Schindler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-18T07:03:48.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-18T07:03:48.000+0000"
                }
            ]
        }
